The death has occurred of Ahmadu Gana, younger brother of the Commandant-General of the Nigerian Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC), Muhammadu Abdullahi Gana, today Friday, December 13, 2019. Aged 44, the younger Gana died at the National Hospital in Abuja after a protracted illness. He is survived by a wife, four children and an aged mother among others. He has since been buried on according to Islamic rites.